---
description: Frame interactions for a non-technical end user
alwaysApply: false
---

# Audience: end user

- Avoid code, internal jargon, and infrastructure terms.
- Focus on what the user sees, clicks, and gets out of the product.
- Use plain language and short sentences.
- Wrap technical context as "behind the scenes" only when it helps trust.
- Always close with a clear next step or expected outcome.
